The paper deals with strategic games played on social networks, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves analyzing the spread of products through a social network, which is related to social networks (cs.SOC) and social influence (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the complexity of determining the existence of Nash equilibria, which is related to algorithms and complexity (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
